2 unit Beyond Meat®
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
226 g Shanghai Bok Choy
30 g Ginger
1 unit Garlic, cloves
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
8 tbsp Teriyaki Sauce
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
2 unit Green Onion
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce. Add 10 cups water and 2 tsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Meanwhile, cut bok choy into 1/2-inch pieces. Thinly slice green onions. Peel, then mince or grate garlic. Peel, then grate 1 tbsp ginger (dbl for 4 ppl).

Add noodles to the boiling water. Cook until tender, 2-3 min. Drain noodles, then rinse under warm water.  Return noodles to the same pot, off heat. Using a pair of scissors, make a few cuts in the pot to cut up noodles. Set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then bok choy and coleslaw cabbage mix. Cook, stirring often, until tender, 5-6 min. Transfer veggies to a large bowl, then cover to keep warm. Set aside.

Heat the same pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then Beyond Meat®, ginger and garlic. Cook, breaking up Beyond Meat®   into smaller pieces, until cooked through and crispy, 5-6 min.** Season with salt and pepper.

Remove the pan from heat, then add veggies, teriyaki sauce, soy sauce and 2 tbsp water (dbl for 4 ppl) to Beyond Meat®. Stir until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min. Add Beyond Meat® and veggie mixture to the pot with noodles. Toss to coat.

Divide Cantonese-style noodles between bowls. Sprinkle green onions over top.